EmailTemplate.name: ADP upgrade campaign
EmailTemplate.subject: ADP Integration Certification
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
{!Account.Name}, ADP is requiring all vendors to complete ADP Integration Certification. This means that as of the near future, they will not be allowing third party “hostel integration” with your DMS. We at Vin Solutions are very excited to announce that we are one of the first to complete our integration certification with ADP.
Below is some information on the benefits of this integration for you and your dealership as well as outlined steps you are required to complete to start the process.
Overview of the improvements to the new ADP integration.
Desking New certified interface is 100% supported and provided by ADP directly. (It is not a hostile or 3rd party solution.) Matches potential existing customers by phone number and last name for dealer to confirm. Can update an existing customer record or create a new customer in ADPPushes Purchase and Lease deals Including full deal structure. Selling price, APR, fees, term, warranty, GAP, etc
Known limitations
Issue with pushing days to first payment (under continued investigation) Accessories/we owes are not pushed (Requires additional integration)Deal push happens within few seconds and returns a deal number
Data pulling
New advanced interfaces for pulling ADP data including Vehicles, F&I Deals, Service ROs, customers, and service appointments Will replace current data polling methodology and will allow pulling more data types, more data fields, and pulling data more often and more reliably
Service Appointments
New ability to pull service appointments in to the DMS Ability to schedule service appointments in MotoSnap and push them to the DMS
ADP is however, passing along a $165 monthly charge for integration as well as a $150 set up fee. Because of your status at Vin Solutions, and in order to move this along quickly, we will be paying the set up fee, and simply passing along the $165 monthly charge on your bill. In the attached directions for how to authorize VinSolutions as a vendor, you will see that when you set the authorization up it has a $0.00 charge. This is simply for the first integration and set up.
Please feel free to call me directly at 1-800-980-7488 x 158, if you have any questions.
Steps for integration (also attached):
STEP 1:Type or click on the link below:
https://portal.dealersuite.com/eStore/faces/pages/customer/index_3PA.jsp?store=VINSolutions
If you are already a member, please skip Step 2.
STEP 2: To login as a new member, you must register first:
1) Click Register Now. Read agreement –click I accept at the bottom of the page to accept usage terms.
2) Enter your CMF number. This is your account number commonly used when opening a case with support. If you do not know your CMF (client number) contact your dealership’s system administrator or contact ADP at 877.483.9171, option 3
3) Enter your user information (name, email, job title, phone, etc).
4) Finish by clicking Add New User.
5) Enter the urlprovided above in Step 1 and continue with Step 3 below.
STEP 3:Enter your ID and Password, then click “login”.
STEP 4:Once logged in, Click “VIN Solutions‘ Integration to ADP Install Now”
STEP 5:Review and select the appropriate product
STEP 6:Click on “Addendum PDF”. Please open and review before proceeding
STEP 7:Click “Add to Cart” (quantity of 1) on the upper right side of the screen
STEP 8:Confirm the quantity for your order then the click “Check Out”. There is no charge for this authorization process and your purchase will display a price of $0.00
STEP 9:Review and print your order, then click “Continue”
STEP 10:Review your billing and shipping information. Enter requested information, then click “Continue”
STEP 11: Complete the process by reading and accepting the agreement. Click “Place my Order Now” to submit your order.
Thank you.Steve Keen1.800.980.7488 x158
